He left Rhinoceros in 1969 and started his solo career shortly after that.

He subsequently moved to Canada and currently lives in Val-David, Quebec.
He was involved in a variety of projects throughout the late '70s and '80s, such as the Bob Dylan movie Renaldo and Clara, but did not record albums during this period.
His productivity as a recording and performing artist has enjoyed a renewal since 1994 and the release of "Chicken walk".
He is almost constantly touring in North America and Europe, sometimes joined by his son Eli and daughter Hannah, who also appear on his 2009 album "Queen of Hearts".
